            <line>Come back home to the refinery</line>
            <line>Hiring man says "son if it was up to me"</line>
            <line>Went down to see my V.A. man</line>
            <line>He said "son don't you understand now"</line>
            <line>Had a brother at Khe Sahn fighting off the Viet Cong</line>
            <line>They're still there he's all gone</line>
            <line>He had a woman he loved in Saigon</line>
            <line>I got a picture of him in her arms now</line>
            <line>Down in the shadow of penitentiary</line>
            <line>Out by the gas fires of the refinery</line>
            <line>I'm ten years burning down the road</line>
            <line>Nowhere to run ain't got nowhere to go</line>
